data.enText: a large glass container in which fish and other water creatures and plants are kept
a building where people can go to see fish and other water creatures

simple_means.memory_skill: aqu 水 + arium 场所，地点 → 水族馆

tr: a tank or pool or bowl filled with water for keeping live fish and underwater animals

value.def: An aquarium is a building, often in a zoo, where fish and underwater animals are kept.
An aquarium is a glass tank filled with water, in which people keep fish.

trans: 乔治亚水族馆；佐治亚水族馆；水族馆
西雅图水族馆；水族馆；西雅圖水族館
